{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Sunshine Ground | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Sunshine Ground | former names = | location = [[Cuttack]], [[Orissa, India|Orissa]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1995 | built = | opened = 1995 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = n/a | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/57968.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''Sunshine Ground''' is a sports venue located in [[Cuttack]], [[Orissa, India|Orissa]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports. The stadium is yet to host [[First-class cricket|first-class]] matches but has hosted five [[List A]] matches <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/973_a.html List A matches]</ref> all in 2001 when [[Bihar cricket team]] played against [[Tripura cricket team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/73/73506.html Scorecard]</ref> The ground hosted four more [[List A]] matches.<ref> [http://www.orissacricket.org/news-details.php?id=ODc0 Odisha venues spotted for BCCI domestic matches]</ref>
The ground has also hosted [[Twenty20]] matches when <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/973_tt.html Twenty20 matches]</ref> all in 2010 when [[Orissa cricket team]] played against [[Tripura cricket team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/297/297672.html Scorecard]</ref> The ground hosted four more [[Twenty20]] matches but since then the stadium has hosted non-first-class matches.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/973_misc.html Other matches]</ref>
